oc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FluxHavoc</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://server2039.virtualave.net/xenoflare/misc/glowball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Artist in Residence</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/8/02 12:33:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3885.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://server2039.virtualave.net/xenoflare/misc/thumb60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I Hate Hands!!!</span><hr size=1> Pretend your hands are gloves. You'd draw them bigger than they normally are but they're easier to draw that way. It's a good way to practice drawing hands and fingers until you get it down properly. <p><embed src="http://xenoflare.virtualave.net/misc/fluxsig2002.swf" width="170" height="60"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uretrotorque.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RetroTorque</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/8/02 9:12:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3885.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/solidnate/sig.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I Hate Hands!!!</span><hr size=1> You can also use a little mirror. Have a study period where you pose your hand in a mirror and draw it. <p>Be well, do good work, and keep in touch. -Writer's Almanac NPR</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/umightyquest.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MightyQUEST</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.pcshelp.com/quest/realm/triforce2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karboni